##Why was Cai Jie, a former member of the Standing Committee of the Wuhan Municipal Party Committee arrested? Large amount of money collected, no epidemic prevention and control

I-CAIJING

CAIJING magazine official Wechat. "CAIJING" magazine, sponsored by the China Securities Market Research Center, was first published in 1998, adhering to the news concept of "independence, exclusiveness and originality" , and is known for authoritative, impartial and professional reporting, it is a must-read publication for policy-makers, researchers and managers in the field of politics and economics.

Authorities said the downfall of a senior official in Wuhan was not related to the outbreak, but was suspected of bribery and abuse of power. In August 2019, he was subject to Disciplinary Review and supervision investigation by the Hubei Provincial Commission for Discipline Inspection and supervision, and was detained

Wen | Caijing reporter, Huang Shujing, Yu Qin, intern Liu Zitong

Editor | Lu Wei

The arrest of a former official at the official level in Wuhan, Hubei Province, has drawn attention at a critical time for the outbreak's prevention and control. On March 11, the Supreme Procuratorate announced that the Han River branch of the Hubei Provincial People's Procuratorate had made an arrest decision against Cai Jie, secretary general of the former Standing Committee of the Wuhan Municipal Party Committee, on suspicion of taking bribes and abuse of power.

According to public information, Cai Jie's arrest has nothing to do with the current epidemic prevention and control. His last public appearance was on August 20,2019. Six days later, on August 26,2019, the Hubei Provincial Commission for Discipline Inspection and supervision announced that Cai Jie was under disciplinary review and supervision investigation by the Hubei Provincial Commission for Discipline Inspection and supervision and that he had been detained on suspicion of serious disciplinary and duty violations.

Now half a year has passed, Cai Jie case is being handled further. According to the relevant departments, Cai Jie was not long ago "double open" , his suspected bribery, Abuse of authority case, by the Hubei Provincial Supervisory Committee investigation concluded, transferred to the procuratorial organs for review and prosecution.

On the evening of March 11,2020, Caijing reporters called the Hubei Provincial Discipline Inspection Commission's Party and Government Work Style supervision office to ask for more details about Cai Jie's arrest. Several people in the room responded that they did not have details of the case.

Cai Jie, 53, a native of Wuhan, Hubei Province, has been in politics for 31 years and has never left his hometown. Before his downfall, Cai was willing to publish articles, participate in television programs and other ways of public expression, high-profile appearance, in the anti-corruption campaign frequently "gold sentence. ". He has written about his "distaste for extravagance, extravagance and behavior, " said he was "ashamed" of complaints on a political television show, and even compared himself to Jiao Yu Lu, "The spirit of struggle and courage are far apart, " he said.

On March 11, CAIJING contacted a Hubei official who had contacted Cai. This personage expresses Cai Jie before falling off a horse to look quite decent,"corrupt official does not see".

It's a huge amount of money

Cai Jie's last public appearance was on August 20,2019. At that time, as a member of the Standing Committee of the Wuhan Municipal Party Committee, secretary-general of the General Office of the Municipal Party Committee, the State Security Office of the Municipal Party Committee, the municipal government organs, party members and cadres lectured party lessons. Cai Jie in his speech stressed that we must adhere to the "strict" word as the head, the combination of learning and application, continue to rectify the formalism, bureaucracy, and strive to forge the practice of the "three models" of the iron army.

Only six days later, on August 26,2019, the Hubei Provincial Commission for Discipline Inspection and supervision announced that Cai Jie was being subjected to disciplinary review, supervision and investigation by the Hubei Provincial Commission for Discipline Inspection and supervision and that he had been detained on suspicion of serious disciplinary and duty violations.

Cai Jie is another incumbent party official in Wuhan who was detained in 2019 following the downfall of Hu Hongchun, former member of the Standing Committee of the Wuhan Municipal Party Committee, Former Secretary of the Work Committee of the Wuhan Development Zone and former secretary of the Hannan District Party Committee. On March 21,2019, Hu Hongchun was investigated for suspected serious disciplinary violations and duty violations. In November of the same year, Hu was indicted on suspicion of taking bribes and abuse of power.

On February 22,2020, the website of the Hubei Provincial Commission for Discipline Inspection and supervision announced that Cai Jie had been expelled from the Party and public office and transferred to the judiciary for punishment according to law.

After a disciplinary review and an investigation by the Hubei Provincial Commission for Discipline Inspection and supervision, Cai Jie was suspected of taking bribes, "In the project to undertake, illegal construction property rights, and other matters to seek benefits for others, directly or through a specific relationship to obtain, illegally accept other people's property, the amount is particularly huge" ; Cai Jie is also suspected of abuse of power for "violating regulations by deciding to allocate financial funds to private enterprises in a particularly serious case" .

According to the disciplinary review and investigation by the Hubei Provincial Commission for Discipline Inspection and supervision, Cai Jie violated political discipline; violated organizational discipline; violated clean discipline; and violated state laws and regulations.

Cai Jie is suspected of taking bribes because he "takes over projects, handles property rights of illegal construction and other matters for the benefit of others" . Before his downfall, Cai published a signed article saying: "Make good decisions on major projects, stick to democratic decision-making, collective decision-making and sunshine decision-making, and prevent corruption in land use and projects. ".

In addition, according to a report published by the Changjiang daily on June 18,2014 under the title "The Democratic Life Meeting of the Standing Committee of the Jiang'an District District Party Committee in Wuhan" , cai Jie, then secretary of the Jiang'an District District Party Committee, took the lead at the meeting by firing a cannon at himself: "I have been working in the team for a long time, the situation in the district is familiar, and the subconscious of taking 'me' as the center has grown up in my mind, sometimes acting on my own will, with a feeling of pride and self-satisfaction and the thought of being eager for quick success and instant benefit. " He was "content only with the completion of economic development projects at the municipal level and the implementation of major projects and major projects. He neglected to lay the foundation and take charge of long-term work. ".

On August 25,2019, the Standing Committee of the Wuhan Municipal Party Committee held a special Democratic Life Meeting on "remembering the original intention and keeping in mind the mission" , take stock of the harvest, examine the problem, deeply analyze. At the meeting, Cai Jie as a member of the Standing Committee of the Municipal Party Committee at that time to make a personal analysis of the speech, "everyone in the speech to open their hearts, speak freely, self-criticism dare to expose the shortcomings. ".

The day after the opening of the Democratic Life Meeting, Cai Jie fell from power.

Once said, "be a good secretary like Jiao Yu Lu. " 

Before Cai Jie was investigated, his official career had been in Wuhan. He has served as secretary of the Wuchang District Party Committee of the Communist Youth League; Member of the Standing Committee of the Wuchang District Party Committee and Director of the Office of the Jiang'an District District Party Committee; Deputy District Governor, Deputy Secretary of the District Party Committee, Acting District Governor, District Governor and District Party secretary. From January 2016 until his arrest, he was a member of the Standing Committee of the Wuhan Municipal Party Committee and Secretary General of the Municipal Party Committee.

Before his downfall, Cai wrote frequently and made a high-profile statement. On April 7,2014, Cai Jie published a signed article in Hubei Daily titled "Be a good secretary like Jiao Yulu. ". In his article, he said that to carry out the spirit of Jiao Yu Lu in the new era and to be a "good secretary" to the satisfaction of the people, we must strengthen three kinds of consciousness, that is, to serve the people wholeheartedly, to strengthen the sense of purpose, to proceed from reality, to strengthen the sense of responsibility; A clean air two sleeves, strengthen the sense of incorruptibility.

On July 14,2014, Cai Jie also published an article in the Hubei daily called "sweeping away the grime of the four winds" , which follows the previous trend, "following the example of Comrade Jiao Yu Lu, and in the light of his pragmatic style, public servant sentiments, fighting spirit and moral sentiment, I have made a thorough examination of and a thorough cleaning of the dirt of my 'four winds' , " Cai said in the article, "compared with Jiao Yu Lu, my working and living conditions have improved a lot, but my fighting spirit and courage are far apart. "

Cai Jie also reflected in the above-mentioned article, "I come from a family of ordinary urban residents, and I am very disgusted with the phenomenon and behavior of extravagance and extravagance, but I am not strong enough in my actual work to oppose and stop some extravagant phenomena. "

In January 2015, Wuhan launched the 2014"ten outstanding issues" campaign, promising to rectify the "final examination" on television. Cai Jie, then the party secretary of Jiang'an District, was involved. According to local media reports, Cai said he was "ashamed" that no one answered the district duty hotline that was exposed by the program at a certain time, and stressed that "the responsibility lies first and foremost with me, this is the district on duty general telephone, I made the commitment that any soldier who makes mistakes is the chief officer who makes mistakes, because I did not take my cadres well. "

Cai Jie, who has repeatedly stressed in public that he wants to be "always clean and honest, " clearly did not resist the temptation. "As a party member and leading cadre, Cai Jie has lost his ideals and beliefs, abandoned his original mission, demanded bribes and accepted bribes, acted without authorization, seriously violated party discipline and state laws, and is suspected of committing crimes, " according to a notice from the relevant department
